<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="honest-adj">honest <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ɒnɪst/    美 /'ɑːnɪst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>老实的；诚实的；正直的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 dishonest </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>An honest man's word is as good as his bond.
诚实人的话就像他的契约书一样靠得住。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>坦白的；直率的</strong></h4>
<p>not hiding the truth about sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's very important to be <strong>honest with</strong> your friends.
对朋友要坦诚，这很重要。</p><footer>外研⑥ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Your answer should be honest.
你应如实回答。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="to-be-honest">to be honest</h3>
<p>1.<strong>老实说：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To be honest, I don't think I was helping very much.
老实说，我认为自己没帮上多少忙。</p><footer>2008 四川</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (老实说), the pay isn't attractive enough, though the job itself is quite interesting.  （2009 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. To be honest / Honestly  </p></div>